Posts Management API
A RESTful API for managing posts with user authentication, built with Node.js, TypeScript, Prisma, and PostgreSQL.

 Features
User Authentication: JWT-based authentication system
Posts Management: CRUD operations for posts
RESTful Design: Follows REST principles and best practices
Type Safety: Built with TypeScript
Database: PostgreSQL with Prisma ORM
Documentation: OpenAPI/Swagger documentation
Error Handling: Comprehensive error responses
Validation: Request validation with proper status codes

Getting Started
Option 1: Local Setup
Clone the repository

Install dependencies

npm install
Configure environment variables
cp .env.example .env

The API will be available at http://localhost:3333/api

 API Documentation
The API documentation is available at:
Swagger UI: http://localhost:3000/api-docs

Testing
Postman Collection
 (https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/31029158/2sB2xFenGp) to test all endpoints.
